@node "A-TRAIN"
A-TRAIN 

During play, type "CHEATERCHEATERWIMP" for $50,000,000.
@endnode
@node "AAARGH!"
AAARGH!

At the start of each screen you'll find various buildings.  Blow fire over
them, and then hit them.  This will make them fall down a lot faster.  When
you burn or knock down a house you get an egg.  To beat the other monsters in
a fight for an egg, don't jump around and breath fire, just hold your ground
and punch forward.  After three or four falls, your foe will stay down.  Keep
eating, even if it dosen't show any increase on screen, your health will
skyrocket.
@endnode        
@node "ABANDONED PLACES 2"
ABANDONED PLACES 2

This cheat will increase your character's experience significantly.  Attack
and kill any single monster (or group of monsters).  When it (or they) begin
to visibly fade away, cast any "hold monster" spell that you have such as
"Dream" or "Hold Everything".  The creature will cease dimming and just sit
there.  Now you can attack with your fighters or cast attack spells
(including "Fire Area") to rake in experience points without worrying that
the monster will go anywhere until the spell wears off.  This can be verified
by watching the experience line in the character sheet grow while you are
attacking the faded creature.  If you are quick enough, you can refreeze the
monster, otherwise just go and find another one to repeat your trick on.

@endnode
@node "ACTION FIGHTER"
ACTION FIGHTER

Get on the hi-score table and enter "ZBACKDOOR" for infinite lives.
@endnode
@node "ADDAM'S FAMILY"
ADDAM'S FAMILY

In case you don't already know....to get 4 free liver each time your game has
ended, walk past the CONTINUE DOOR to the left and there is a room where you
can collect them!

Go up immediately into the hall of rooms, walk left until you are under the
door above you...push up.  You are now in a secret room.  Collect the stuff
in that room, THEN walk up directly up that door and push up--there you will
find a MASS amount of treasures, 1 UPS, and other goodies!

Useful codes in the game (not sure where you use them)

  First power-up    &1#1# (&1#1F)?    L1191 - extra energy
  Second power-up   ?1S1M             61H1C - rescue Pugsley
  Third power-up    BLSRS             B&198 - rescue Granny
  Pugsley           V121B             B?KKV - rescue Fenster
  Wednesday         VD2RL             BLS1T - rescue Wednesday
  Granny            V&YKW
  Fester            VL#R4             (Second column from Amiga Power)

                     ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

The following codes will start you off in certain places. (Amiga Action)

  &1Y1M  - 3 hearts (after the big tree)
  ?191D  - Hearts (after fridge in kitchen)
  B919D  - 5 hearts (after conservatory)
  V1S14  - Pugsley (Games room)
  V919B  - Fenster (Picture Gallery)
  BG9K&  - Wednesday (Crypt)
  BLJK#  - Granny (Kitchen)
@endnode
@node "AFTER THE WAR"
AFTER THE WAR

To give yourself infinite energy & time, press the following three keys
simultaneously on level 1:

Hold down the 'ALT', '1', 'B'  keys.

Holding down the  'ALT', '1', 'M'  keys advances you to the second level.

The password for Level 2 is 101069.
@endnode
@node "AFTERBURNER"
AFTERBURNER

For the U.K. version:
--------------------
Pause the game , then type THUNDERBLADE. Then try the following keys:

  < - Go down a level
  > - Go up a level
  G - More Missiles
  T - Less Missiles
  N - Extra Lives

Fly to the top of the screeen to avoid missiles.  Slow down on levels 8 and
17 to avoid rocks.  Go full speed to dodge infra-red missiles.

Note: Other sources say type TOGETHER IN ELECTRIC DREAMS


For the U.S.A. version:
----------------------
Fly to the top of the screeen to avoid missiles.  Slow down on levels 8 and
17 to avoid rocks.  Go full speed to dodge infra-red missiles.  The cheat key
for the U.K. version also works!
@endnode
@node "AGONY"
AGONY

During play:

Press 'F1' to place a sword beneath the owl.

Press 'F2' to place the sword above the owl.

Press 'F3' to increase the size of the blasts you can fire.

Press 'F4' three times to gain an extra live.  This cheat can be repeated as
often as neccessary.

Note: Another sourse says you need to type "FANTASY", first then press 'F1'
- 'F5' for various cheats.  Pressing the 'Return' key will then skips levels.
@endnode
@node "AIRBALL"
AIRBALL

The spellbook is in the room with the candle.  You have to pick up and
remove the blocks to get it.  Take the spellbook back to the start screen
and drop it in the top left corner and follow the instructions to get the
ingredients to complete the game.
@endnode
@node "ALFRED CHICKEN"
ALFRED CHICKEN

On the title screen, type "HELPMARK" for a level select screen.  Press '1'
- '9' or 'A' - 'B' to select the level you want.

On level one go through the first door as usual.  Then go to the far right
bottom and jump up to go through a secret wall to get a special weapon.  Then
exit.  When you re-appear, jump on the spring at the bottom left and just as
you start flying upwards push up so that you hit an invisible block with a
door on it.  Now go to the right across the floating platforms, but instead
of going through the door as normal, stand on the edge above the door and
fire the weapon.  Another invisible block should appear jump on this block.
Then jump up left and walk across the top of the screen to the first secret
block and go through the door and you will enter a secret warp room.  
@endnode        
@node "ALIEN 3"
ALIEN 3

Go to the Options screen and select Hard and 6 Credits.  Then pressing the
'SPACE' and 'N' keys simultanously in the game should propel you up a level.
@endnode
@node "ALIEN BREED"
ALIEN BREED

To activate the following cheats, log on at the terminal  to the Intex
computer on deck two (one screen south of where you start) and simply type in
(including spaces) one of the following:

"I CANT BE ARSED TO PLAY THE FIRST LEVELS" - sends you directly to deck 3
"ALIENS ARE FAGGOTS" - makes the aliens quite weak
"PUFFNUTS MODE" - makes the aliens quite slow
"IS IT TRUE THAT THE ALIENS SUPPORT MAN UTD" - makes the aliens very weak
"PISSED AS A FART" - to play the game in drunken mode
"PITBULLS ON THE LOOSE" - makes the aliens as dangerous as pitbull terriers
"BEN JOHNSON TRAINED THESE ALIENS" - makes the aliens a bit faster
"THE IRAQIS MADE THE WEAPONS" - gives you absolutely abysmal weapons
"SALMAN RUSHIE PLAYS ALIEN BREED" - makes player invisible
"BEWARE ALIENS SPADGE HAS DROPPED ONE" - makes aliens run away

The best method of disposing of the end of level guardians is to stay at the
very bottom of the screen and continously shoot at the nasties.  The
guardians will almost touch you at times, but if you stay firmly at the
bottom, they won't harm you.

For  various  comedy  messages  try  these  out: "GAMESX", "FULL CONTACT",
"LEEDS", "SPADGE", "GALLUP", "LIVERPOOL", and "NEWCASTLE BROWN".
@endnode
