@node "ANTEP"
ANTEP

Go to the nearest town and offer your items for sale.  When asked which items
you should attempt to sell press '1' - '5'.  These items are non-existant,
but the shopkeeper give you lots of gold.  Repeat this as many time as you
like.  Don't hit any number above 5 or the game will crash!
@endnode        
@node "A.P.B."
A.P.B.

Type ALF into the hi-score table for infinite demerits.

If you hold down the button while driving, the siren will sound, and the
other cars will move out of the way.  Now you can drive at full speed without
crashing.

You can start playing the game on any of the 16 levels, if you press the fire
button and push forward on the joystick while the music is playing!
@endnode
@node "APIDYA"
APIDYA

Pause the game and type "ULRDABBA" for full weaponry (this only works once.  
If you type it again you'll lose a life.  To advance to the next stage, type
in the following codes on the titles screen and press 'Enter':

     Stage:     Code:
     ---------------------
       2     MISSHONEYBEE
       3     DEPUTYOFLOVE
       4     HASTALAVISTA
       5     SNEAKPREVIEW
      END    SHOWCREDITS
      
When you press 'HELP' and 'DEL' at the same time the on-screen action will
slow down approximately 50%.
@endnode
@node "APPRENTICE"
APPRENTICE

During play, press and hold 'DEL' and 'F3' for 50 guys and all the extras.
Press 'TAB' after the first title screen and you can use any of these level
passwords: "WIZARD", "SPELLS", "ARCANE", "DRUID", or "FAERIE".
@endnode
@node "ARCTIC FOX"
ARCTIC FOX

The following is a list of the locations that you may start at when playing
the Tournament level:

Key             Starting Locations
----------------------------------------------
F1              53'33"  82'08"
F2              55'25"  82'24"
F3              56'14"  82'56"
F4              54'49"  83'41"
F5              51'45"  83'50"
F6              50'21"  83'34"
F7              49'41"  83'11"
F8              50'49"  82'18"

Some other helpful hints are:

Under configuration F3 & place F4 there is a Communication Fort at
coordinates 54'12",83'16".  The fort is behind the mountain and guarded by a
missle launcher and several tanks.

Under configuration F1 & place F7 to the east of the coordinates 53'30",
83'36", the Main Complex is located there and is guarded by several missle
launchers and lots of heavy tanks.
@endnode
@node "AQUAVENTURA"
AQUAVENTURA

On options screen, hold down 'CTR'L & 'F10' keys, then press fire to start.
You can now skip levels by pressing 'L' and can skip to the tunnel section by
pressing 'T'.
@endnode
@node "ARABIAN NIGHTS"
ARABIAN NIGHTS

On the title screen, type "SIMEON" and during the game use the following
keys:

  'F1'  - Gives you the power sword.
  'F10' - Pal/NTSC.
  'TAB' - Skips levels.
   'H'  - Slow motion.
   'E'  - English.
   'F'  - French.
   'G'  - German.
   'D'  - Dutch.
   
Hold down the 'LEFT AMIGA KEY' for invincibility or when you need a key to
open a door or a crank.
@endnode        
@node "ARCHER M'S POOL"
ARCHER M'S POOL

Type "VF12" while in trickshot mode, then go to demo mode to find the new
menu.  Select two players to make the computer play itself, then wait.  Now
the computer's controlled players abilities are revealed.
@endnode        
@node "ARCHIPELAGOS"
ARCHIPELAGOS

When asked to select an Archipelagos choose "8421" then press the 'ENTER' key
twice.  Now you can select any island from 1 to 9999.

Another source says you must play the first two levels before activating
the above sequence.
@endnode
@node "ARCTIC FOX"
ARCTIC FOX

The following is a list of the locations that you may start at when playing
the tournament level:

                        KEY     STARTING    LOCATIONS
                ----------------------------------------------
                       'F1'      53'33"      82'08"
                       'F2'      55'25"      82'24"
                       'F3'      56'14"      82'56"
                       'F4'      54'49"      83'41"
                       'F5'      51'45"      83'50"
                       'F6'      50'21"      83'34"
